{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]The greatest of love songs are the ones you never [F]hear
[G7]They're written in the dark of night and each note is a [C]tear
[F]You might find them on a pillow or on a glass down at the bar
[C]But this love song was [G7]written on a tear stained [C]guitar
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]A tear stained guitar tells the story of my [C]life
[D7]About the two who had their fling left me to pay the [G7]price
[C]If I live to be a hundred and have the fortunes of a [F]star
[C]Still I won't forget you and [G7]my tear stained [C]guitar
{end_of_verse}

